<subSubSection id="C3481CACF37AFFDEFF2D21D396AB5D28" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED4F27F37AFFDEFF2D21D396AB5D28" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B9269335F37AFFDEFF2D21D3932F5D53" bold="true" box="[199,315,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">Remarks.</emphasis>
The forewing venation with all veins free is consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5234A4F37AFFDEFBCF21D396A95D53" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1910" box="[1061,1213,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Homaloxestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9269335F37AFFDEFBCF21D396A95D53" box="[1061,1213,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">Homaloxestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the hindwing venation with M2 absent differs from that of congeners. However, the male genital characters are consistent with those of the genus, and these provide ample evidence that the species belongs to 
<emphasis id="B9269335F37AFFDEFBF5226696AB5D28" box="[1055,1215,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">
<taxonomicName id="4C5234A4F37AFFDEFBF5226696AF5D28" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1910" box="[1055,1211,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Homaloxestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Homaloxestis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3481CACF37AFFDEFF2D224297145DCC" box="[199,1280,622,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED4F27F37AFFDEFF2D224297145DCC" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,647]" box="[199,1280,622,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">
